pproval by LC Bank and payment of any applicable renewal fees.&#10;&#10;6. Documentation and Compliance:&#10;   - LC Bank will ensure that all documentation related to Letters of Credit complies with applicable laws, regulations, and international banking standards.&#10;   - Applicants are responsible for providing accurate and complete documentation to facilitate the issuance and processing of LC transactions.&#10;&#10;7. Dispute Resolution:&#10;   - In the event of disputes arising from LC transactions, LC Bank will endeavor to resolve them in a fair and timely manner.&#10;   - Disputes may be resolved through negotiation, mediation, or other alternative dispute resolution methods as agreed upon by all parties involved.&#10;&#10;8. Confidentiality and Data Security:&#10;   - LC Bank will maintain the confidentiality and security of all information provided by applicants in accordance with applicable laws and regulations.&#10;   - Applicants' information will only be disclosed to authorized parties for the purpose of processing LC transactions or as required by law.&#10;&#10;9. Termination of Services:&#10;   - LC Bank reserves the right to terminate or suspend LC services to any applicant for reasons including but not limited to non-compliance with terms, default on payments, or legal/regulatory requirements.&#10;&#10;10. Amendment of Terms and Policies:&#10;    - LC Bank reserves the right to amend these terms and policies at any time, with prior notice to affected parties.&#10;    - Amendments will be communicated through appropriate channels, and continued use of LC services will constitute acceptance of the revised terms.&#10;&#10;By using the Letter of Credit Management System provided by LC Bank, applicants agree to abide by these terms and policies. For further clarification or inquiries, applicants may contact LC Bank's customer service department.&#10;">
